{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "health-e2e",
    "name": "Health (GET /health)",
    "description": "E2E tests for GET /health.\n\nHandler behaviour (health.go):\n  • Without ?ping=true  — fast path for load-balancer probes: 200 {status:'ok'}\n  • With    ?ping=true  — parallel service probes: 200 {status,pong:true,services[]} when all up; 503 when any probe is down\n\nFolder execution order (orchestrated by make e2e-health):\n  1. smoke          — fast-path shape, ?ping=true shape + probe fields, security headers\n  2. rate-limiting  — 429 after bucket exhaustion (Makefile flushes Redis before this folder)\n\nRate-limiter config (routes.go): burst=10, rate=30/min (0.5 tok\/s) per IP.\nRetry-After = ceil(1 \/0.5) = 2 s.\nThe rate-limiting folder sends 10 warmup GETs to drain the bucket, then the 11th must 429.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "smoke",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /health → 200 {status:ok}",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const b = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('body.status is ok', () => pm.expect(b.status).to.eql('ok'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "health"]
            }
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "GET /health?ping=true → probe body shape (200 all-up or 503 degraded)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var b = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('HTTP status is 200 or 503', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 503]);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('body.status is ok or degraded', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.status).to.be.oneOf(['ok', 'degraded']);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('HTTP code matches body.status', function() {",
                  "  if (b.status === 'ok') { pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200); }",
                  "  if (b.status === 'degraded') { pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(503); }",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('body.pong is true', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.pong).to.eql(true);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('body.services is a non-empty array', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.services).to.be.an('array').with.lengthOf.above(0);",
                  "});",
                  "(b.services || []).forEach(function(svc, i) {",
                  "  var tag = 'services[' + i + '] (' + svc.name + ')';",
                  "  pm.test(tag + '.name is a non-empty string', function() {",
                  "    pm.expect(svc.name).to.be.a('string').and.have.lengthOf.above(0);",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test(tag + '.status is up or down', function() {",
                  "    pm.expect(svc.status).to.be.oneOf(['up', 'down']);",
                  "  });",
                  "  if (svc.latency_ms !== undefined) {",
                  "    pm.test(tag + '.latency_ms is a non-negative number', function() {",
                  "      pm.expect(svc.latency_ms).to.be.a('number').and.to.be.at.least(0);",
                  "    });",
                  "  }",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Database probe present', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.services.some(function(s) { return s.name === 'Database'; })).to.be.true;",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Redis probe present', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.services.some(function(s) { return s.name === 'Redis'; })).to.be.true;",
                  "});",
                  "var REQUIRED = ['Database', 'Redis'];",
                  "var down = (b.services || []).filter(function(s) { return s.status === 'down'; });",
                  "var downRequired = down.filter(function(s) { return REQUIRED.indexOf(s.name) !== -1; });",
                  "var downOptional = down.filter(function(s) { return REQUIRED.indexOf(s.name) === -1; });",
                  "if (downOptional.length > 0) {",
                  "  var optMsg = downOptional.map(function(s) { return s.name + (s.detail ? ' (' + s.detail + ')' : ''); }).join(', ');",
                  "  console.warn('INFO: optional services not running (expected in dev): ' + optMsg);",
                  "}",
                  "if (downRequired.length > 0) {",
                  "  var reqMsg = downRequired.map(function(s) { return s.name + (s.detail ? ' (' + s.detail + ')' : ''); }).join(', ');",
                  "  pm.test('REQUIRED services down: ' + reqMsg, function() {",
                  "    pm.expect(false, 'Required services are down: ' + reqMsg).to.be.true;",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/health?ping=true",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "health"],
              "query": [{"key": "ping", "value": "true"}]
            }
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "GET /health → security headers present",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff', () =>",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('X-Content-Type-Options')).to.eql('nosniff')",
                  ");",
                  "pm.test('X-Frame-Options: DENY', () =>",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('X-Frame-Options')).to.eql('DENY')",
                  ");"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "health"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "rate-limiting",
      "description": "Burst=10 (NewIPRateLimiter rate=30/60 burst=10). Send 10 warmups to drain the bucket, then the 11th must 429. Requests fire with --delay-request 1 so refill (0.5 tok/s ≈ 1 token per 2 s) is negligible between rapid back-to-back calls.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "warmup 1/10 — consume slot (→ not 429)",
          "event": [{"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('not rate-limited yet (slot 1)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.not.eql(429));"]}}],
          "request": {"method": "GET", "header": [], "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/health", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "health"]}}
